<HEAD>URGENT</HEAD>
<HEAD>CAPE CANAVERAL, Fla.: the cause.</HEAD>
<TEXT>
   A computer system had taken control of the countdown 31 seconds
before the planned ignition. When it detected the problem, it
automatically sent a signal to stop the firing sequence.
   The shutdown signal came ``just after the go for main engine
start was issued,'' Harris said.
   It was another major disappointment for shuttle program managers
who have been grooming Discovery for the first shuttle flight since
the loss of Challenger and its crew of seven in an explosion 73
