<HEAD>Coastal City Threatened by Forest Fire</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BELGRADE, Yugoslavia (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A major forest fire threatened the
Adriatic industrial city of Sibenik, disrupted traffic and knocked
out electricity, it was reported Thursday.
   The blaze near the city of 50,000 people was being aggravated by
a strong southerly wind, the official Tanjug news agency said.
   Traffic on the coastal highway 40 miles north of the
mid-Adriatic port of Split was detoured.
   It was the first major blaze reported this year on the Adriatic
coast which had been afflicted by extensive fires two years ago.
The cause of the fire was not known, Tanjug said.
