<HEAD>Brazilian Trade and Industry Minister, 62</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BRASILIA, Brazil (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Jose Hugo Castelo Branco, Brazil's Trade
and Industry minister, died Thursday after a long battle with
intestinal cancer, the ministry said. He was 62.
   President Jose Sarney declared three days of official mourning
for Castelo Branco, who died at Brasilia's armed forces hospital,
the ministry said.
   Castelo Branco had held the post since February 1986.
Previously, he was civilian liason minister for Sarney's government.
   The presidential palace said a replacement has not been named.
   Sarney took office in March 1985, ending 21 years of military
rule.
