<DOCNO> AP880804-0162 </DOCNO>
<FILEID>AP-NR-08-04-88 1142EDT</FILEID>
<1ST_LINE>r f Ingersoll-RandElectsNewChairman     08-04 0129</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>Ingersoll-Rand Elects New Chairman</2ND_LINE>
<DATELINE>WOODCLIFF LAKE, N.J. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Ingersoll-Rand Co. has named
Theodore H. Black as its new chairman and chief executive officer,
the company's board of directors announced today.
   Current chairman Thomas A. Holmes, who has headed the company
since January 1981, plans to retire Sept. 30. Black's appointment
is effective Oct. 1.
   Black, 59, had been president and chief executive officer of
Dresser-Rand Co., a joint venture of Ingersoll-Rand Co. and Dresser
Industries. He was elected president and chief operating officer of
Ingersoll-Rand in February.
   Ingersoll-Rand is a leading manufacturer of industrial
machinery, construction equipment, bearings, door hardware and
security systems.
   The company, which reported sales last year of $2.6 billion,
employs 30,000 people in 72 plants in the United States and other
countries.
