<HEAD>Production Goes Down This Week</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DETROIT (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Domestic automakers were scheduled to produce
142,706 cars and light trucks this week, down from last week's
144,956, Ward's Automotive Reports said Thursday.
   This week's planned production is higher than the same week a
year ago, in which 139,427 cars and light trucks were produced, the
trade journal said.
   U.S. automakers were scheduled to make 77,646 cars this week,
compared with 73,532 a week ago and 70,796 in the same week in 1987.
   Light truck production for the week was scheduled at 65,060,
compared with last week's 71,424 and last year's 68,631.
   Canadian automakers were to build 9,148 cars this week, down
from 9,577 a week ago and up from last year's 1,387.
   Canadian light truck production was scheduled at 11,511,
compared with 8,941 a week ago and 11,493 in the same week last
year.
