<HEAD>London Stocks Up</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: UPDATES thruout with closing stocks, comment.</NOTE>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Share prices rose Thursday on the London Stock
Exchange, boosted by takeover talk and some interest from major
financial institutions.
   The Financial Times-Stock Exchange 100-share index rose 4.6
points, or 0.25 percent, to 1,869.7, just below the day's high of
1,870.5 at early afternoon.
   Trading volume rose to 472.3 million shares, compared with
Wednesday's 416.1 million shares.
   A handful of stocks were active on takeover speculation, dealers
said, but most issues were fairly inactive.
   Some dealers said they detected a greater amount of
participation by institutions and funds. But one salesman said,
``They're still mainly sitting on their hands.''
   The Financial Times 30-share index was up 6.5 points at 1,508.5
at the close. The Financial Times 500-share index rose 2.95 points
to close at 1,067.23.
</TEXT>
