<HEAD>Dun & Bradstreet Acquiring American Credit Indemnity</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Dun & Bradstreet Corp. said Thursday it plans to
acquire Commercial Credit Co.'s 97-year-old business credit
insurance subsidiary for $140 million in cash.
   American Credit Indemnity Co., based in Baltimore, will fit
within Dun & Bradstreet's credit risk management services, the
announcement said.
   The deal is subject to government approval.
   American Credit had after-tax profit of $11.2 million in 1987.
Founded in 1891, it insures customers' trade receivables against
excessive bad-debt losses stemming from insolvency of its customers.
   Commercial Credit Co. said American Credit no longer fit into
its long-term strategy.
</TEXT>
