<1ST_LINE>r f BC-SportsIllustrated     08-04 0171</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>BC-Sports Illustrated,0177</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Sports Illustrated To Launch Children's Magazine</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Sports Illustrated announced Thursday it is
launching a new magazine for children, with the first edition
planned for next January.
   The magazine, to be called Sports Illustrated for Kids, will be
targeted to children age 8 and older and has two aims, the
announcement said.
   ``The editorial purpose will be to emphasize the enjoyment that
exists in all sports, whether the reader is a participant or
spectator,'' said Mark Mulvoy, managing editor. ``In the process,
it will improve reading, learning and socialization skills.''
   The magazine's initial circulation of 500,000 will be equally
divided between paid home subscriptions and distribution to 2,500
schools participating in the Sports Illustrated for Kids literacy
program, the announcement said.
   Sports Illustrated, which is published by Time Inc., said it has
lined up 20 of a hoped-for 36 corporate sponsors. Each of the
sponsors will make an annual commitment of $250,000 and receive 10
pages of advertising and participation in the literacy program.
</TEXT>
