<1ST_LINE>r f AM-GTE-Stock     08-04 0246</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-GTE-Stock,0253</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>GTE Authorizes Repurchase of Common Stock</HEAD>
<DATELINE>STAMFORD, Conn. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   GTE Corp. said Thursday its board has
authorized the repurchase of up to 25 million shares of its common
stock, which is part of a plan the company began two years ago.
   GTE said the repurchase will be made from time to time on the
open market. These acquired shares will be used primarily to
satisfy GTE's various employee and shareholder stock-purchasing
plans in 1989 and 1990, the company said.
   ``Today's actions strongly support GTE's primary financial
objective, which is to maximize our shareholders' total return on
their investment,'' said GTE Chairman and Chief Executive Office
James L. Johnson.
   ``These actions are particularly appropriate in light of the
sale of 30.1 percent of US Sprint, announced several weeks ago, and
the elimination of the uncertainity of US Sprint's performance on
GTE's earnings outlook,'' he said.
   GTE announced in July an agreement with United
Telecommunications Inc. that calls for GTE to sell a 30.1 percent
interest in US Sprint Communications Co. to United at book value as
of Dec. 31, 1988. The estimated book value is about $600 million.
GTE and United Telecommunications have owned the long-distance
telephone company equally since July 1, 1986.
   United Telecommunications also has the option of purchasing
GTE's remaining 19.9 percent interest in US Sprint until Dec. 31,
1995. GTE has the option of requiring United to purchase its
remaining interest between Dec. 31 1991 and Dec. 31, 1995.
